                        "description": "1 \u00b5l of derivatives was injected in split mode with a ratio of 10:1, and the solvent delay time was set to 2.2 min. The initial oven temperature was held at 50 \u00baC for 2 min, ramped to 70 \u00baC at a rate of 10 \u00baC/min, to 85 \u00baC at a rate of 3 \u00baC/min, to 110 \u00baC at a rate of 5 \u00baC/min, to 290 \u00baC at a rate of 30 \u00baC/min, and finally held at 290 \u00baC for 8 min. Helium was used as a carrier gas at a constant flow rate of 1 ml/min through the column. The temperatures of the front inlet, transfer line, and electron impact (EI) ion source were set at 260, 290, and 230 \u00baC, respectively. The electron energy was -70 eV, and the mass spectral data was collected in a full scan mode (m/z 30-600).",
